A=\pi R^2
A = 2\int\limits_{-R}^{R}\sqrt{R^2-t^2}dt
t=R\sin\theta
-\frac{\pi}{2}\leq \theta\leq\frac{\pi}{2}
R^2 - t^2 = R^2(1-\sin^2\theta) = R^2\cos^2\theta
\sqrt{R^2-t^2} = \sqrt{R^2\cos^2\theta} = |R\cos\theta| = R\cos\theta
R\geq 0
\cos\theta\geq 0
\theta\in[-\frac{\pi}{2},\frac{\pi}{2}]
t=R\sin\theta
dt = R\cos\theta\,d\theta
t=-R
\theta=-\frac{\pi}{2}
t=R
\theta=\frac{\pi}{2}
\int_{-R}^R\sqrt{R^2-t^2}\,dt = \int_{-\frac{\pi}{2}}^{\frac{\pi}{2}}R\cos^2\theta\,d\theta.
\sin^2\theta
1-\cos^2\theta
\int \cos^2\theta\,d\theta = \frac{1}{2}\theta + \frac{1}{2}\sin\theta\cos\theta+C
